This is the Ruy Lopez. Very old opening found in manuscripts from the middle ages. White influences the center by attacking the knight that controls d4,e5.

I have been exploring this move, known as the Schliemann Defense. Not seen much in top level games. but it seems to have some tactics. Much like a Kings gambit reversed perhaps. Other moves possible here are: Nd4 Bird's Defense, d6 Steinitz Defense, Bc5 Cordel Defense,  Nf6 Berlin Defense, a6 Morphy Defense. 
I am also fond of Gambit play, and this seems to gambit a pawn.
